# Autonomous Workflow

When given a task, complete it end-to-end without stopping to ask "what's next?" or "shall I continue?".

## Rules

- After completing a step, immediately proceed to the next logical step
- Use the TodoWrite tool to plan multi-step tasks upfront, then execute all of them
- Only stop to ask the user when:
  - A genuine ambiguity exists that could lead to two very different outcomes
  - Credentials, secrets, or destructive operations are involved
  - The task is complete
- Do NOT ask for confirmation between steps — just keep going
- Do NOT summarize what you "will do next" — just do it
- If you encounter an error, attempt to fix it yourself before reporting
- When finishing, provide a concise summary of everything that was done
